xeno.remoting.web

Class Response

  • java.lang.Object
    • xeno.remoting.web.Response

  • public class Response
extends Object

    A wrapped HttpServletResponse object, integrated and encapsulated the original HTTP servlet response methods. This object just provides those methods which are most frequently using in the web application, you could call method getOriginalHttpServletResponse() to get the original HTTP servlet response instance you are current using.

    Author:
    Kai Feng

    • Method Detail

      • getOriginalHttpServletResponse

        public javax.servlet.http.HttpServletResponse getOriginalHttpServletResponse()

        Returns the original HTTP servlet response instance you are current using. Because the feature of the AJAX based web application, stream data (handled by the MessageServlet during each request), traditional URL dispatch (No any URL redirect or dispatch), or status reset (override by the MessageServlet during each response) will no longer keep behaviors as before.

        Returns:
        The object, never be null.
